originalText.text:
My other Alma mater! This building is really great, lots of comfortable working place, screening room, cabaret style space in the basement, patio out back. It's perfect.

I think it used to be a museum as well. I've spoken here as well. The staff are all wonderful. AV is great...we did pop a projector bulb mid speech, but those things have a lifespan. They gotta die at some point.

originalText.text:
Definitely one of the best college experiences in the world (if not THE best if you take advantage of all its offerings). Turns NYC into your learning playground. Highlights:
1. Cultural passport that gets you into the best venues and museums for free.
2. Priority course registration at your CUNY campus home base, but with the option to take any class offered over the 8+ CUNY campuses.
3. Graduate without debt, free to pursue your passion.

As a former student, I was skeptical going in. 4 years later, thanks to Macaulay's resources, I've been put on my current path, directing a science education nonprofit straight out of college.

originalText.text: The best college experience you can get. Free Mac, tuition, and study abroad money and a great education at a CUNY school right in the middle of NYC.

originalText.text: Being an alum of the Macaulay Honors College, I have to say that I'm glad I decided on the Macaulay Honors College. With FREE tuition, a FREE Apple laptop, a $7500 opportunity fund which can be used for study abroad, our own advisors, honors classes that are cross campus and this beautiful building that students can use as a spot to study, have club meetings, etc, it is one of the best decisions I have made, without being in debt after graduation.  The Macaulay Honors College also hosts public events that invite some of the best known authors and celebrities for book readings, such as R.L. Stine and Carla Hall.
